<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="19" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis box="[199,325,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="30">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name “oxalida” is used to emphasize the 
<typeStatus box="[834,882,944,970]" pageId="19" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
locality “Oxapampa” and the observation that the species is lighter (= “pallida” in Latin) than the putative sister species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balint" authorityYear="2003" box="[935,1085,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Johnsonita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="johnbanksi">
<emphasis box="[935,1085,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="30">J. johnbanksi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species name “oxalida” is freely formed Latin name and is treated as a female noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
